column2: Air temp 80 F.  Calm.  Mostly sunny.  Some clouds.
Air temp 71 F.  Partly cloudy and west wind 10 mph.
wind 15 to 20 MPH-  partly sunny. Not much boat traffic.
Water level a bit low. Everything still ok. No algae blooms noticed yet.

column1: No boats- sunny- breezy- cold this morning---low 40's
Algae throughout water column
Loon pair and otter swimming around raft at my place (NW shore) yesterday

column2: 67.4 degree air temp. Mostly sunny- SSW wind- nice spring day. Saw an otter crossing the lake this morning. Heard a loon the day before. Water looked clean and clear. Two docks in so far. Lynn helped with the data.
Air Temp 69 F Overcast- Slight SW breeze - 2 boats fishing
Assisted by Lynn- Air Temp 70.8 F- Mostly Cloudy- Windy ssw 10 -15 mph- No other boats - one loon off shoreline by Villa Venice
Data and sample collected by Jerry Mroczkowski- Assisted by Isaac Krueger-  Air temp 60 degrees-  Overcast w/ occasional drizzle- Slight wind SSE
Assisted by Lynn- 69.8 Air Temp- Mostly sunny- Wind NNW- Humidity dropping- No visible signs of algae growth. No other boats on lake- 3 otters in bay off of our south dock
Jerry Mroczkowski- Bob Sundell- Air Temp 82.9- Scattered Clouds- Slight Breeze WSW- Beautiful day

Beautiful blue sky day with a few clouds in the afternoon. High of 73 degrees F and wind from the north at 1 mph.  Sam and I discovered P.L. while we were monitoring Squaw Lakes entire shoreline for AIS and obtaining water quality data.  Sam obtained GPS coordinates while I collected several specimen samples- which included root stock. Afterwards- the specimen samples were delivered to the DNR for verification- It was a beautiful blue sky day with a few clouds in the afternoon. Temp high was 73 degrees F and wind out of the north at 1 mph.   Blue skies- high of 73 degrees F- and wind from the north at 1 mph
Jerry Mroczkowski- assisted by Aiden Krueger- Air Temp. 73 degrees- Mostly cloudy- windy ssw- slight amount of blue-green algae on my north and south shore
Bob Sundell- Jerry Mroczkowski- 64 degrees air temp- Calm NNW- Clear skies- Some algae visible- 3 loons
assisted by Lynn Sundell- Rowed out to sample site. Air temp 66 degrees- sunny w/ high clouds- windy SSE- occasional gust- beautiful day. Loon on lake. Ice out 4/01. Took phosphorus sample.
Taken by Bob Sundell- Satellite day- Air Temp. 50 degrees- Overcast- West breeze with occasional gust. One other boat on lake fishing. FOY hummingbird.
Assisted by Lynn Sundell- Air temp. 71.6- Clear + Breezy. 3 1/2" of rain the last few days. "Popple fuzz" and slight algae along shoreline.

Assisted by Nick Raasch- Air temp. 74.6- Breezy from West- Clear. Pine Dust and alge accumulating on my South shore but cleared out by West wind this morning. Yesterday saw loon chick w/ parents on west shore near small island. Saw a doe on west shore south of Squaw Creek outlet
Assisted by Walker Mroczkowski- Aidan + Isaac Krueger- Allison Raasch. Air temp. 85.2 degrees- south breeze- humid- hazy clouds- beautiful day. No signs of algae. Water looks great!.
Satellite day. Assisted by Lynn Sundell. Air temp. 81.6 degrees- partly cloudy- breezy SSW. No visible signs of algae.
Assisted by Bob Sundell. Satellite Day. Air Temp. 79.5 degrees- clear sky- calm wind- beautiful day- algae showing up and collecting along my south shore. Saw adult and juvenile loon.

Jerry Mroczkowski + Bob Sundell- Satellite day- collected August sample for Phos + Chlor. Air temp. 72.8 degrees. Windy WSW- partly cloudy. Saw adult loon feeding juvenile loon small fish. Juvenile loon staring to show some color.

column1: Not seeing any accumulating algae along the shoreline.

column2: Bob + Lynn Sundell  Air Temp 70.1 degrees F. Mostly cloudy. Strong wind from south

Bob + Lynn Sundell- Air temp. 68.3- mostly cloudy- slight algae along south shore- beautiful fall colors Bob + Lynn Sundell- Air temp. 68.3- mostly cloudy. This morning - slight algae along my south shore. Beautiful fall colors
Data taken by Bob + Lynn Sundell. Air temp. 52.3 degrees. Partly sunny to slight overcast. Breezy NE. 2 plus inches of snow on 4/28.
Bob + Lynn Sundell  Air Temp. 85 degrees- Mostly cloudy- wind SSW12 gust to 23

Bob + Lynn Sundell- Air temp. 64.7- Breezy WNW- Cloudy tp part cloudy and occasional shower or downpour.  Feels like Fall- Lots of rain past month.  Two boats fishing- one touring pontoon. Sampled for Phos. + Chl.
Bob + Lynn Sundell- Satellite day- Lake like glass- Very slight breeze from West- Partly to mostly cloudy- Air temp. 82.2- Saw loon family- one baby

Jerry Mroczkowski- Jamie McElhenny- Gavin Sundell- Bob Sundell. Sampled for Phos. + Chlor. Air temp. 76 degrees- Breeze ESE- clear sky- beautiful day. Water looks clear. No signs of algae. Tips of rocks showing in "triangle" area off point. Sea gulls sitting on rocks.

Bob Sundell- Isaac + Aiden Krueger. Satellite day. Air temp. 69.2 degrees- Breeze from North- Clear sky w/ few scattered clouds. Beautiful day. No signs of algae. Large fish surfaced about 5' from Secchi. Heavy larger boat traffic in the afternoon.

column1: 8/13 Noticed  "clotting"  blue green algae along my South shoreline.
8/14 "Clotting" blue green algae no longer visible. But very slight suspended algae can be seen.
8/15  Water looked clear this morning

column2: Jerry Mroczkowski- Bob Sundell. Sampled for Phos + Chlor- Air temp. 60.8- windy north. Partly sunny- feels like Fall. No visible signs of algae.

9/13/17 Bob Sundell + Jerry Mroczkowski- Satellite day- 82.4 air temp.- south breeze- clear sky- wispy clouds in west- suspended algae- accumulation of algae along my South shore. Saw adult and juvenile loon. 2 otters by Fuller Creek outlet. Geese gone. Fewer hummers. Trees turning. Beautiful!!

column1: 9/14 No algae along South or North shore. Less suspended algae today

column2: Air Temp. 64.5- South wind- clear sky. 4" rain began 6:00 PM Fri. ended Sat. about 6:00 PM. Lake level came up about 4" to a high level. On Friday and Saturday observed surface and suspended algae along both North and South shorelines.

column1: Monday morning surface algae was no longer seen. Less suspended algae was seen. Water looked much cleaner. Probably from "flushing". Dam head looked about 4" - 6".

column2: Phosphorus sample and data taken by Bob and Lynn Sundell. Ice off May 4th reported by Diane Zanski.

column1: Air temp. 67.8 degrees. Partly sunny- windy from North.
2 pair of loons on the lake. Saw 2 trumpeter swans on Squaw Creek on bend before dam.

column2: Bob + Lynn Sundell- Isaac Krueger. Satellite day. air temp. 76 degrees. Mostly overcast- Breezy ESE. A deer standing on shoreline by Mudpuppy Point. 2 eagles in dead birch tree just West of Villa Venice. Loon off shore by Villa. Lake is quiet with one other boat out fishing.

Jerry Mroczkowski and Bob Sundell- Sampled for Phos + Chlor. Air temp 80.4- Partly sunny- high clouds- wind calm SE. Water very high from rains June 14th thru 17th. Lake was up 12" to 13" from low levels. Several dock sections and pallets floating.

column1: But water looked very nice. Occasional pine pollen at shoreline. Lake is quiet. 2 small fishing boats.

column2: Jerry Mroczkowski- Bob Sundell. Air temp. 84 degrees- Mostly sunny- Slight breeze West- Beautiful day. Caught crappie limit of 5 each medium size. Lake quiet. Water beautiful. Very warm weather last 2 weeks. Water level back to normal. Almost no rain last 2 weeks.
Jerry Mroczkowski- Isaac Krueger- Bob sundell. Air temp 64 degrees- mostly sunny- Stiff wind from North.
Data taken by Jerry Mroczkowski. Also on boat: Linda Mroczkowski- Lynn and Bob Sundell.

column1: Air temp. 82.7 degrees- Hazy- partly cloudy. Calm wind. Beautiful day. Single loon on lake. Bug hatch  and very slight algae seen along south shore. North shore water looked clear. While kayaking along shorelines - no algae signs.

column2: Jerry Mroczkowski- Bob Sundell. Collected for PHOS + CHLO. 81 degrees air temp.- overcast- windy from South. Quier on lake - no boats. Thundershower overnight- 3/8" rain. Water looked very nice. Very slight algae along my South shore this morning. North shore very clear.
Bob and Lynn Sundell- Air temp. 54 degrees- overcast. Saw one loon.

Bob and Lynn Sundell. Phosphorus sample taken. Ice off April 26th. Beautiful day. Air temp 64 degrees. Breeze NNE. DNR put in a Fyke net off our North shoreon Monday.  Brought their catch to our dock for Lynn and me to see. 3 large muskies- 2 walleyes ( 1 about 28" w/ large girth)- a few gills and perch- about 25 crappies. DNR techs were very informative.

Bob and Lynn Sundell- Air temp 74 degrees- Mostly sunny. Lake is high. Lots of rain. Some pine pollen on water surface at South shore. Able to kayak further up Squaw Creek this morning due to high water.
Bob and Lynn Sundell.- Air temp. 76.4- intermittent sun- quiet on lake

Bob + Lynn Sundell- Jerry + Haakon Mroczkowski. Air temp 76 degrees- mostly sunny- breezy from West. Quiet on lake. No other boats. Sampled for Phos. + Chlor. No signs of algae. Mayfly hatch and lots of dragonflies.

Bob + Lynn Sundell- Air temp. 76 degrees- Slight North breeze- Clear sky but hazy from Canadian wildfires. Can smell smoke. A few boats. A lot of boat and PWC traffic the last few days. Water looked good. Now algae sign.

Jerry Mroczkowski- Bob + Lynn Sundell. Phos. + Chlo. sampled. Quality Assurance sampling. Air temp. 68 degrees. Breeze WNW. Sunny w/ scattered clouds. No signs of algae.  Water at low/normal. Seagull sitting on rocks at triangle.

Bob + Lynn Sundell- Air temp. 79 degrees- breeze SSW- Scattered clouds- beautiful day. Suspended algae- some slight algae collecting off our South shore then dissipating.  Bob + Lynn Sundell- Air temp. 79 degrees- Breeze SSW- scattered clouds- fog earlier- burned off about 9:30. Beautiful day. Suspened algae. Some algae accumulated off my South shore then dissipated. Lake quiet.

Jerry Mroczkowski- Bob + Lynn Sundell- Sampled for Phos. + Chlor. Air temp. 72.5- Partly cloudly- breezy- SE. Water appeared a bit murky from algae. No accumulation of algae along shoreline. Signs of otters on our North dock. Saw eagle pick up fish from lake and settle in tree in front of Jerry's place.
Bob + Lynn Sundell. Air temp. 62.4 degrees- Mostly cloudy- Windy WNW- Water is high. Storms last night - 2 1/2" rain.

column1: Suspended algae. 4 otters playing off of our North dock. Saw one loon.

column2: Bob + Lynn Sundell- Air temp. 53.6- breeze from North. Mostly sunny. 4 ft. Secchi. Water very clear. Isaac + Aidan Krueger - Nick Raasch also on boat. No Phos. or Chlo. sample taken. Covid 19 rules in place until May 26. Quiet on lake. But a few kayakers. Saw an eagle and hawk in midair tussle then locked together in freefall about 50 ft. Counted more than 25 turtles on sunny side of Squaw Creek shore just around bend from lake outlet. Saw 2 loons and an otter. Beaver active on our North shore. Took down a 5" diameter popple.
Bob + Lynn Sundell- Phos./ Chlor. sampled.  Air temp. 79 degrees- mostly sunny- horsetail clouds- breeze SW. Beautiful morning. Water clear. secchi at 4 ft. Fishing slow.
Bob- Lynn- Gavin- Peyton Sundell. Air temp. 90.6 degrees. Mostly sunny- slight breeze South. Very warm for the past week. Water quality has been very good. Clear with no visible signs of algae.
Bob Sundell- Isaac  + Aidan Krueger. Phos. + Chlor. sampled. Air temp. 79.5 degrees. partly cloudy. Breeze SSW. No visible signs of algae.

Bob and Lynn Sundell. Phos. + Chlo. sampled.  Air temp. 83. Mostly sunny- windy South. Water color darker than earlier in the season. Had a good amount of rain June and July. Some visible algae but slight. Saw one loon.
Bob + Lynn Sundell- 1st  day of Fall. Air Temp. 79.3- Sunny- clear. Beautiful day. Tree colors are gloriously vibrant!!
